snippet.textDisplay:
2019 was one of the worst years I ever had for my mental health.
I mentally broke myself struggling and worrying about not having a job. I tried so hard to get something, anything... and it was always met with the same response. Always something along the lines of "We've decided to move forward with other candidates at this time" or "You're not qualified for this position." All of that worrying killed me, and nearly drove a wedge between me and my wife.

I've decided that 2020 is going to be different. I'm still going to try, but I'm also going to live my life to the fullest and stop worrying about my circumstances. I'm not going to let 2020 break me. I'm going to move forward in life, doing what I love doing, and I'm not going to let anyone or anything bring me down.

This year, I'm going to forge myself into a better me.
